# vdti enforces these patterns to prevent kels-era terminology and
# rejected-design-direction terms from leaking back into the codebase.
# Each line is a regex (grep -E). The lint-terminology script walks all
# .terminology-forbidden files in the tree; deeper files REPLACE
# shallower ones for their subtree.

# === Removed primitives (post-kels#214 simplification) ===
# Cnt removed; per-node Contested removed; upgrade rule removed.
\bCnt\b
\bis_contested\b
\bupgrade[ _]rule\b

# === Removed identifiers (post-kels#218 federation trust model) ===
# Static trusted prefix list replaced with federation Fcp SAID set.
\bTRUSTED_REGISTRY_PREFIXES\b
\bTRUSTED_REGISTRY_MEMBERS\b

# === Rejected design directions (post-kels#218) ===
# Federation-Dip / Fip ruled out — federation IEL uses Fcp self-signing carve-out.
\bFederation-Dip\b
\bFip\b

# === Renamed services (kels consolidation) ===
# sadstore + kels-service consolidated into vdtid; gossip-service → witnessd.
\bsadstore\b
\bkels-service\b
\bgossip-service\b
\bkels-sadstore\b

# === kels-internal tool / agent names (out-of-context in vdti) ===
# Distinctive enough to forbid; common words ("max", "min") rely on review.
# xhigh is allowed — it names a real Claude Code effort tier in PROCESS.md.
\bclaudit\b

# === kels protocol namespace leakage ===
# vdti has its own namespace: vdti/witness/v1/topics/*, vdti/sad/v1/*, etc.
kels/gossip/
kels/witness/
kels/sad/

# === Retired IEL policy model (post-iel-policies-audit) ===
# Two-field authPolicy / governancePolicy replaced by the PoliciesSet model
# (policies["governance"] / ["delegation"] / ["sel"] + app-level kinds).
# "governance-authorized" conflated policy (who) with tier (auth level) — the
# two axes are named separately now (see protocol-doctrine.md
# §Policy and tier are orthogonal axes).
\bauthPolicy\b
\bgovernancePolicy\b
governance-authorized
